{
  "text": "For the complexity of the M -partition problem for chordal graphs, we derive the following result. Proof: According to Theorems 6.1 and 6.2 from [CITATION_1] , all matrices M which do not contain C 3 or its complement have polynomial M -partition problems. This proves the claim for any matrix without three diagonal 0's or three diagonal 1's (such as the matrix mentioned above). For matrices with three diagonal 0's or three diagonal 1's and size m < 5, the matrix C has only one row or one column and so it is automatically crossed, thus the M -partition problem is polynomial by [CITATION_2] .",
